data.description: Motivated seller will pay $12,450 in closing costs with full price offer. Beautiful Fayette County home in the family friendly Stonebriar subdivision community with well maintained and land scaped yard. The front walkway stretches along the side entry garage to the covered front porch sitting area, with views of the swimming pool, tennis courts, pavilion, playground, and walking trails across the street.  Through the front door you’ll be greeted by an open 2 story foyer with luxury solid surface flooring throughout the main level, tastefully detailed half bathroom on the left, and large formal dining room on the right. Straight ahead to the open living room with towering ceilings and fireplace, that flows into the large eat in kitchen area. With granite counter tops, deep shelved pantry, matching 4-piece stainless steel appliance set, and plenty of cabinet space; you’ll love the kitchen. The owner’s suite is also on the main floor with tray ceiling, garden tub, separate shower, dual vanities, closed off water room, and large walk-in closet. Upstairs there are 2 spacious secondary bedrooms with tray ceilings, a full bathroom with double vanities and isolated tub and shower space. The large loft/office area has a built-in desk workspace, and cabinets to handle all work from home needs without sacrificing a room. The 3rd room upstairs has framed glass French doors and is currently being used as a study and family room but could easily be a 4th bedroom.
